ObAgent: uncertain

Reason: traces show elevated inter-service latencies (p95/mean rises), but metrics include a diskio anomaly on ts-auth-service and a latency metric on ts-order-service — this could be service-side CPU/blocking I/O or network problems. To disambiguate, check:
- whether_is_abnormal_metric for host.cpu.* (cpu.utilization), host.mem.used_percent, and disk metrics (disk.io.time / read/write latency) on affected hosts; 
- whether_is_abnormal_metric for network indicators (net.tcp.retransmits, net.if.*.drop/errors, tcp.rtt);
- collect_trace on ts-price-service and ts-contacts-service to see span breakdown (time in app vs network/wait).
JudgeAgent: No - There is strong metric evidence of a ts-auth-service disk I/O spike (diskio=1.661e+05 at 2024-01-23 15:40:00, sev=20.9) and widespread inter-service trace p95/latency spikes (e.g., ts-order-service latency-90 rise), but the root-cause criteria are not fully met: the service-location rule requires confirmation that all ts-auth-service pods are anomalous (no per-pod diskio/pod-level confirmation provided) and other candidate failures (order-service latency and broad trace increases) were not ruled out. Therefore the location/type/reason are not conclusively pinned down.

